:{{see|microscopium}}

==English==
===Etymology===
Named by the French [[astronomer]] Nicolas Louis de Lacaille in 1763. From later {{L.}} ''[[microscopium]]'', a "[[microscope]]"

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Microscopium'''

#{{constellation}}: A faint [[constellation]] of the [[southern]] [[spring]] sky, said to resemble a [[microscope]]. It lies south of the [[constellation]] of [[Capricornus]].

